{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1798,"text":"I was three months pregnant with twins"},{"time":4295,"text":"when my husband Ross and I\nwent to my second sonogram."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9221,"text":"I was 35 years old at the time,"},{"time":11563,"text":"and I knew that that meant\nwe had a higher risk"},{"time":14907,"text":"of having a child with a birth defect."},{"time":17907,"text":"So, Ross and I researched\nthe standard birth defects,"},{"time":20989,"text":"and we felt reasonably prepared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23973,"text":"Well, nothing would have prepared us"},{"time":25942,"text":"for the bizarre diagnosis\nthat we were about to face."},{"time":30291,"text":"The doctor explained\nthat one of our twins, Thomas,"},{"time":33854,"text":"had a fatal birth defect\ncalled anencephaly."},{"time":37476,"text":"This means that his brain\nwas not formed correctly"},{"time":40894,"text":"because part of his skull was missing."},{"time":43663,"text":"Babies with this diagnosis\ntypically die in utero"},{"time":47211,"text":"or within a few minutes, hours\nor days of being born."},{"time":53013,"text":"But the other twin, Callum,"},{"time":56252,"text":"appeared to be healthy,\nas far as the doctor could tell,"},{"time":60164,"text":"and these twins were identical,"},{"time":64355,"text":"genetically identical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68125,"text":"So after a lot of questions about\nhow this could have possibly happened,"},{"time":72761,"text":"a selective reduction was mentioned,"},{"time":75921,"text":"and while this procedure\nwas not impossible,"},{"time":78846,"text":"it posed some unique risks\nfor the healthy twin and for me,"},{"time":83228,"text":"so we decided to carry\nthe pregnancy to term."},{"time":87101,"text":"So there I was, three months pregnant,\nwith two trimesters ahead of me,"},{"time":91316,"text":"and I had to find a way to manage\nmy blood pressure and my stress."},{"time":97268,"text":"And it felt like having a roommate\npoint a loaded gun at you for six months."},{"time":103553,"text":"But I stared down\nthe barrel of that gun for so long"},{"time":108507,"text":"that I saw a light\nat the end of the tunnel."},{"time":111506,"text":"While there was nothing we could do\nto prevent the tragedy,"},{"time":114634,"text":"I wanted to find a way\nfor Thomas's brief life"},{"time":117121,"text":"to have some kind of positive impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119366,"text":"So I asked my nurse about organ,\neye and tissue donation."},{"time":124080,"text":"She connected with our local\norgan-procurement organization,"},{"time":127625,"text":"the Washington Regional\nTransplant Community."},{"time":131359,"text":"WRTC explained to me"},{"time":133954,"text":"that Thomas would probably be too small\nat birth to donate for transplant,"},{"time":138379,"text":"and I was shocked:"},{"time":139553,"text":"I didn't even know\nyou could be rejected for that."},{"time":141981,"text":"But they said that he would be\na good candidate to donate for research."},{"time":146290,"text":"This helped me see Thomas in a new light."},{"time":148345,"text":"As opposed to just a victim of a disease,"},{"time":151264,"text":"I started to see him as a possible key\nto unlock a medical mystery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156288,"text":"On March 23, 2010,"},{"time":159590,"text":"the twins were born,\nand they were both born alive."},{"time":163978,"text":"And just like the doctor said,"},{"time":165668,"text":"Thomas was missing\nthe top part of his skull,"},{"time":168771,"text":"but he could nurse,"},{"time":170318,"text":"drink from a bottle,"},{"time":171794,"text":"cuddle and grab our fingers\nlike a normal baby,"},{"time":175117,"text":"and he slept in our arms."},{"time":178053,"text":"After six days, Thomas died in Ross's arms"},{"time":181466,"text":"surrounded by our family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184846,"text":"We called WRTC, who sent a van to our home"},{"time":189005,"text":"and brought him to Children's\nNational Medical Center."},{"time":192751,"text":"A few hours later, we got a call to say\nthat the recovery was a success,"},{"time":196596,"text":"and Thomas's donations\nwould be going to four different places."},{"time":200159,"text":"His cord blood would go\nto Duke University."},{"time":203208,"text":"His liver would go to a cell-therapy\ncompany called Cytonet in Durham."},{"time":208263,"text":"His corneas would go\nto Schepens Eye Research Institute,"},{"time":211532,"text":"which is part of Harvard Medical School,"},{"time":213715,"text":"and his retinas would go\nto the University of Pennsylvania."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218083,"text":"A few days later, we had a funeral\nwith our immediate family,"},{"time":222035,"text":"including baby Callum,"},{"time":224003,"text":"and we basically\nclosed this chapter in our lives."},{"time":227718,"text":"But I did find myself wondering,\nwhat's happening now?"},{"time":231055,"text":"What are the researchers learning?"},{"time":233130,"text":"And was it even worthwhile to donate?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237019,"text":"WRTC invited Ross and I\nto a grief retreat,"},{"time":240765,"text":"and we met about\n15 other grieving families"},{"time":243542,"text":"who had donated their loved one's\norgans for transplant."},{"time":247494,"text":"Some of them had even received letters"},{"time":249919,"text":"from the people who received\ntheir loved one's organs,"},{"time":252912,"text":"saying thank you."},{"time":255038,"text":"I learned that they\ncould even meet each other"},{"time":257251,"text":"if they'd both sign a waiver,"},{"time":258713,"text":"almost like an open adoption."},{"time":260907,"text":"And I was so excited,\nI thought maybe I could write a letter"},{"time":263770,"text":"or I could get a letter\nand learn about what happened."},{"time":266403,"text":"But I was disappointed to learn"},{"time":267966,"text":"that this process only exists\nfor people who donate for transplant."},{"time":271160,"text":"So I was jealous.\nI had transplant envy, I guess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274446,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276104,"text":"But over the years that followed,"},{"time":278024,"text":"I learned a lot more about donation,"},{"time":280524,"text":"and I even got a job in the field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282626,"text":"And I came up with an idea."},{"time":285879,"text":"I wrote a letter that started out,"},{"time":287562,"text":"\"Dear Researcher.\""},{"time":290468,"text":"I explained who I was,"},{"time":292342,"text":"and I asked if they could tell me\nwhy they requested infant retinas"},{"time":296234,"text":"in March of 2010,"},{"time":298493,"text":"and I asked if my family\ncould visit their lab."},{"time":301953,"text":"I emailed it to the eye bank\nthat arranged the donation,"},{"time":305073,"text":"the Old Dominion Eye Foundation,"},{"time":307475,"text":"and asked if they could\nsend it to the right person."},{"time":310395,"text":"They said that they had\nnever done this before,"},{"time":312650,"text":"and they couldn't guarantee a response,"},{"time":314563,"text":"but they wouldn't be an obstacle,\nand they would deliver it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318506,"text":"Two days later, I got a response"},{"time":320721,"text":"from Dr. Arupa Ganguly\nof the University of Pennsylvania."},{"time":324617,"text":"She thanked me for the donation,"},{"time":326263,"text":"and she explained\nthat she is studying retinoblastoma,"},{"time":329010,"text":"which is a deadly cancer of the retina"},{"time":330851,"text":"that affects children\nunder the age of five,"},{"time":333001,"text":"and she said that yes,\nwe were invited to visit her lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336612,"text":"So next we talked on the phone,"},{"time":338278,"text":"and one of the first things she said to me"},{"time":340349,"text":"was that she couldn't possibly\nimagine how we felt,"},{"time":343204,"text":"and that Thomas had given\nthe ultimate sacrifice,"},{"time":345968,"text":"and that she seemed\nto feel indebted to us."},{"time":348709,"text":"So I said, \"Nothing against your study,"},{"time":351859,"text":"but we didn't actually pick it."},{"time":353549,"text":"We donated to the system,\nand the system chose your study."},{"time":357493,"text":"I said, \"And second of all,\nbad things happen to children every day,"},{"time":362407,"text":"and if you didn't want these retinas,"},{"time":364219,"text":"they would probably\nbe buried in the ground right now."},{"time":366773,"text":"So to be able to participate in your study"},{"time":370163,"text":"gives Thomas's life\na new layer of meaning."},{"time":373830,"text":"So, never feel guilty\nabout using this tissue.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":377845,"text":"Next, she explained to me how rare it was."},{"time":380403,"text":"She had placed a request\nfor this tissue six years earlier"},{"time":384123,"text":"with the National Disease\nResearch Interchange."},{"time":387160,"text":"She got only one sample of tissue\nthat fit her criteria,"},{"time":390518,"text":"and it was Thomas's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392958,"text":"Next, we arranged a date for me\nto come visit the lab,"},{"time":396712,"text":"and we chose March 23, 2015,\nwhich was the twins' fifth birthday."},{"time":402563,"text":"After we hung up, I emailed her\nsome pictures of Thomas and Callum,"},{"time":406523,"text":"and a few weeks later,\nwe received this T-shirt in the mail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411142,"text":"A few months later, Ross, Callum\nand I piled in the car"},{"time":413965,"text":"and we went for a road trip."},{"time":415580,"text":"We met Arupa and her staff,"},{"time":418168,"text":"and Arupa said that when I told her\nnot to feel guilty, that it was a relief,"},{"time":422440,"text":"and that she hadn't seen it\nfrom our perspective."},{"time":426090,"text":"She also explained that Thomas\nhad a secret code name."},{"time":430931,"text":"The same way Henrietta Lacks\nis called HeLa,"},{"time":434324,"text":"Thomas was called RES 360."},{"time":437394,"text":"RES means research,"},{"time":438816,"text":"and 360 means he was the 360th specimen"},{"time":442340,"text":"over the course of about 10 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445133,"text":"She also shared with us a unique document,"},{"time":449300,"text":"and it was the shipping label"},{"time":451809,"text":"that sent his retinas\nfrom DC to Philadelphia."},{"time":456273,"text":"This shipping label\nis like an heirloom to us now."},{"time":460304,"text":"It's the same way that a military medal\nor a wedding certificate might be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464687,"text":"Arupa also explained that she is using\nThomas's retina and his RNA"},{"time":470111,"text":"to try to inactivate the gene\nthat causes tumor formation,"},{"time":473545,"text":"and she even showed us some results\nthat were based on RES 360."},{"time":477959,"text":"Then she took us to the freezer"},{"time":479817,"text":"and she showed us the two samples\nthat she still has"},{"time":483276,"text":"that are still labeled RES 360."},{"time":485622,"text":"There's two little ones left."},{"time":487506,"text":"She said she saved it"},{"time":489058,"text":"because she doesn't know\nwhen she might get more."},{"time":492553,"text":"After this, we went to the conference room"},{"time":494625,"text":"and we relaxed and we had lunch together,"},{"time":497259,"text":"and the lab staff presented Callum\nwith a birthday gift."},{"time":502179,"text":"It was a child's lab kit."},{"time":504419,"text":"And they also offered him an internship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506831,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510038,"text":"So in closing, I have two\nsimple messages today."},{"time":513578,"text":"One is that most of us probably\ndon't think about donating to research."},{"time":517406,"text":"I know I didn't.\nI think I'm a normal person."},{"time":520540,"text":"But I did it."},{"time":521715,"text":"It was a good experience,\nand I recommend it,"},{"time":523881,"text":"and it brought my family a lot of peace."},{"time":525849,"text":"And second is if you work\nwith human tissue"},{"time":528658,"text":"and you wonder about the donor\nand about the family,"},{"time":531277,"text":"write them a letter."},{"time":532496,"text":"Tell them you received it,\ntell them what you're working on,"},{"time":535336,"text":"and invite them to visit your lab,"},{"time":537027,"text":"because that visit may be\neven more gratifying for you"},{"time":539576,"text":"than it is for them."},{"time":540831,"text":"And I'd also like to ask you a favor."},{"time":542617,"text":"If you're ever successful\nin arranging one of these visits,"},{"time":545600,"text":"please tell me about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548064,"text":"The other part of my family's story"},{"time":549784,"text":"is that we ended up visiting\nall four facilities"},{"time":552120,"text":"that received Thomas's donations."},{"time":554206,"text":"And we met amazing people\ndoing inspiring work."},{"time":558003,"text":"The way I see it now\nis that Thomas got into Harvard,"},{"time":563128,"text":"Duke and Penn --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565318,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":568667,"text":"And he has a job at Cytonet,"},{"time":571059,"text":"and he has colleagues and he has coworkers"},{"time":573868,"text":"who are in the top of their fields."},{"time":575653,"text":"And they need him\nin order to do their job."},{"time":579137,"text":"And a life that once seemed\nbrief and insignificant"},{"time":583812,"text":"revealed itself to be vital,\neverlasting and relevant."},{"time":590224,"text":"And I only hope that my life\ncan be as relevant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593512,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594687,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}